{"author":"RebarBotNava","data":{"fields":{"description":"# Event-sourced enrichment queue: cert-triggered enqueue, 60-min soak, latest-wins, lock-guarded claim\n\n## Why\nEnrichment must be async and off the hot write path. rebar's event store is already a durable, shared, serialized-write queue substrate ‚Äî better than a bolted-on SQLite/broker (which cannot live on a shared path nor be visible to all clients). Modeling the queue as sidecar events makes \"a new certification replaces the old entry\" the natural latest-wins reduce.\n\n## What\nThree sidecar events keyed by `ticket_id`, reduced to queue state:\n- `ENQUEUE_ENRICH` `{ticket_id, not_before_ns}` appended on plan-review CERTIFICATION, `not_before_ns = cert + SOAK` (SOAK default 60 min). A re-cert appends a new one that supersedes the prior (latest-wins by HLC) and bumps `not_before_ns` ‚Äî the soak/debounce as a stored timestamp filtered at drain, NOT an in-process timer.\n- `CLAIM_ENRICH` `{ticket_id, drainer_id, lease_expires_ns}`, `DONE_ENRICH` `{ticket_id}`.\n- Reducer `pending_enrichment(now_ns)` ‚Üí entries past soak, unclaimed-or-lease-expired, with no later DONE.\n\n## Atomicity + claim (accurate to the store's ACTUAL locking model ‚Äî DERISKED)\nThe store exposes a MANUAL compound lock ‚Äî `lock.acquire(tracker, timeout=30, dual_window=True) -> LockHandle` / `LockHandle.release()` (`src/rebar/_store/lock.py`), used by `src/rebar/_commands/txn.py::_acquire_write_lock` to run \"ONE critical section in ONE process: acquire the lock, append event file(s), release only at the end\" (txn.py:10-22). This is NOT `stage_and_commit`/`write_and_push` (which re-acquire per event). Two consequences, both confirmed by inspecting the code:\n- **Atomic enqueue:** the certification write and its `ENQUEUE_ENRICH` are appended in ONE `txn`-style critical section (both under one held lock), so there is no certified-but-unqueued gap.\n- **Race-free claim:** the drainer's claim is READ-REDUCE-CHECK-THEN-APPEND inside a single held `lock.acquire` critical section ‚Äî re-reduce the ticket's queue state, and only if still unclaimed/expired append `CLAIM_ENRICH`. Exactly one drainer wins; the loser re-reads and picks another.\nLease `LEASE_TTL` (default 15 min); a claim with `lease_expires_ns < now` is treated as unclaimed on the next drain (self-healing, no separate reaper process). Defense-in-depth fallback (owned/implemented by the S4 drain, see below): the drain ALSO treats a ticket that is certified but whose digest is absent/stale as implicitly enqueable, so even a crash between cert and ENQUEUE cannot permanently miss it.\n\n## Scope (exact edit targets)\n- `src/rebar/_store/event_append.py` `EVENT_TYPES` (+ StoreError message): add the three types. `src/rebar/reducer/_version.py`: add to `_NON_REPLAY_KNOWN_TYPES` (sidecar; like REVIEW_RESULT/TICKET_DIGEST).\n- Enqueue hook + the atomic cert-critical-section in `src/rebar/llm/plan_review/` certification path, using `lock.acquire` (the txn pattern) and the HLC clock for `not_before_ns`.\n- Config: `overlap_soak_min` (60), `overlap_lease_ttl_min` (15) on `LLMConfig` (`[tool.rebar.llm]`, `REBAR_LLM_OVERLAP_*`) ‚Äî LLM-feature tunables, not `VerifyConfig`.\n- This story owns ENQUEUE + CLAIM + the reducer. It does NOT own DONE-emission, the growth-bound retention, or the self-healing scan ‚Äî those require the drain runner and are OWNED BY S4 (leggy-heedless-mosquito).\n\n## Dependencies\nS2 (wispy-cheerless-tick) for the digest freshness the enqueue/drain consult. S4 owns the drain that appends DONE + runs the fallback scan.\n\n## Testing\n- `tests/unit/test_enrich_queue.py`: `test_enqueue_and_recert` (not_before = cert+SOAK; re-cert supersedes+bumps); `test_soak_and_latest_wins` (pending honors soak + ‚â§1/ticket); `test_claim_race` (two claimers in one critical section ‚Üí exactly one CLAIM lands); `test_atomic_enqueue` (cert + ENQUEUE in one lock ‚Äî no gap); `test_lease_reclaim` (expired lease reclaimable, idempotent).\n\n## Acceptance Criteria\n- [ ] Certifying appends `ENQUEUE_ENRICH` with `not_before_ns = cert + SOAK`, atomically with the cert write under one `lock.acquire` critical section; re-cert supersedes+bumps; `pytest ...::{test_enqueue_and_recert,test_atomic_enqueue}`.\n- [ ] `pending_enrichment(now)` returns only past-soak, unclaimed-or-expired, ‚â§1/ticket; `::test_soak_and_latest_wins`.\n- [ ] Two concurrent claimers ‚Üí exactly one `CLAIM_ENRICH` lands (read-reduce-check-append inside one held lock); loser retries; `::test_claim_race`.\n- [ ] Lease-expired claim reclaimable on next drain (self-healing); re-processing idempotent; `::test_lease_reclaim`.\n- [ ] The three event types are in `EVENT_TYPES` + `_NON_REPLAY_KNOWN_TYPES`. (DONE-emission, growth-bound, and the self-healing scan are S4's ACs, not this story's.)\n"}},"env_id":"ade0f2ef-51cc-45a2-bb97-c09846cd3df5","event_type":"EDIT","timestamp":1783623198505604001,"uuid":"2bd63749-e26d-4466-9a3b-89d4d8283989"}